\title{Definition: Subgroup}
\date{2025-05-08}
\taxon{Definition}
\meta{parent}{gt-subgroups}

\p{A subset #{H \subseteq G} is a \strong{subgroup} if it is closed under the group operation and inverses, and contains the identity. Equivalently: #{H \neq \emptyset} and #{a b^{-1} \in H} for all #{a, b \in H}.}
